{ This is White's most flexible option. Black must be ready for either a quick d2-d4 or the calmer d2-d3. Let's talk about some other options which won't be trainable:   4.O-O  Nf6  5.d4  Transposes to the 4. d4 line.  5...Bxd4   4.Nc3  This transposes into the 4.d3 line.  4...Nf6  5.d3  d6  And we're back in the Canal Variation.   4.Ng5  This is a good move against the Two Knights Defense, but after 3...Bc5 it just loses the game.  4...Qxg5  Black wins a piece! }
