10... Ba7
{ Black can't safely capture the a5-pawn, but the bishop is secure on a7 now that White has no way to open the a-file.   10...Nxa5  This capture allows White a dangerous sacrifice.  11.Rxa5  Bxa5  12.dxe5  Nxe4  This almost works, but there's a tactical flaw.   12...dxe5  doesn't work either after  13.Qxd8+  Kxd8  14.Nxe5  .  13.Qd5  Be6  Black defends f7 and skewers to win the bishop on b3.  14.Qxe4  Bxb3  15.Nd4  Ouch! White attacks b3 and also aims to fork three different black pieces with Nc6. Black's in trouble.   10...Bxa5??  11.d5  Black loses a piece. }
