Qe7+ { White has no comfortable way to meet this check. } 7. Kf1
{ Now White will have a difficult time getting the h1-rook into the game. }
7... Ne5 { Black saves the knight and attacks the white bishop. } 8. Qxd4
{ Now White's ahead by a pawn, but Black is the one attacking. } 8... Nxc4
{ Eliminating a dangerous attacking piece. } 9. Qxc4 h6
{ Putting an end to the white attack. } 10. Nf3 Qc5
{ Again, Black forces away White's only well-placed piece. Even in the endgame, Black will have a dangerous attack. }
11. Qxc5 Bxc5
{ The bishop finds its favorite square and the d5-pawn is vulnerable. } 12. Nc3
Bf5
{ White has no good way to defend c2 and Black is also ahead in development. White's position is already close to lost. }
