{ White exchanges in the center, but the counter-attack on a2 keeps Black in good shape. }
13... cxd5 { It's best to capture with a pawn and attack the white bishop. }
14. Nxd5 { White forces a long series of exchanges. } 14... Bxd5 15. Bxd5 Nxd5
16. Qxd5
{ White is temporarily up a pawn, but Black can win it back without trouble. }
16... Qxd5 { Trading into a comfortable ending. } 17. Rxd5
{ Now Black wins back a pawn with no problems in the endgame. } 17... Rxa2
{ This endgame is even although Black managed to win in Xiong,J @@StartBracket@@2659@@EndBracket@@ -Melkumyan,H @@StartBracket@@2640@@EndBracket@@ chess.com INT 2024. }
