6... Bb6
{ It's nice to be able to recapture toward the center with the a-pawn. } 7.
Nxb6 axb6 { Black activates the a8-rook. } 8. c3
{ White gets ready to support an eventual d3-d4 advance, but Black is ready to break the pin, with a very safe position. }
8... Bd7
{ Black breaks the pin on the knight and is ready to castle, with an even game. }
