[White "5) Odds & Ends"]
[Black "Center Game: 2.d4 / 3.Qxd4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5
{ In this chapter we will examine all of White's unusual choices on move two.   None of these are popular at higher levels, but you never know what you will run into in any given game, so it helps to be a bit prepared. You don't need to memorize these lines very deeply, but we will go into some detail, just to make sure you're ready if you know that an opponent plays one of the sharper gambits. }
2. d4
{ The Danish Gambit can lead to fireworks if Black gets greedy, but we aren't going to let White gain a dangerous lead in development. }
2... exd4 3. Qxd4
{ This is the Center Game.   A few aggressive players like to try it on occasion, but developing the queen early rarely works out well.   3.Nf3  You can play ...Bc5 if you want to take the game in a new direction, but there's also no reason to avoid 3...Nc6 to transpose directly into the Scotch Game.  3...Nc6  transposes to a Scotch Game. }
3... Nc6 { Let's develop and attack the white queen. } 4. Qe3
{ This is by far the most popular square for White's queen. On the e-file it discourages Black's ...d7-d5 advance because the pawn will capture with a discovered check. }
4... Nf6 { Let's just keep developing. } 5. e5
{ This agressive move looks dangerous, but it would be shocking if White's queen and pawn based attack was dangerous without any minor pieces involved. }
5... Ng4 { Black saves the knight and forks White's queen and e5-pawn. } 6. Qe4
{ White keeps attacking the g4-knight, but Black can sacrifice it for enourmous compensation. }
6... Ngxe5
{ White must aim to win the e5-knight. Otherwise Black is just up a pawn. } 7.
f4 { White breaks more opening principles, but will eventually win a knight. }
7... d5 { Black gains time on the exposed white queen. } 8. Qe2
{ White maintains the pin. } 8... Bb4+ 9. c3
{ Black has two pieces in danger, but White's plan of only developing the queen is doomed to failure. }
9... O-O { White can win a piece or two, but Black soon wins the white queen. }
10. fxe5 Nxe5 { Black clears the e-file for a deadly attack. } 11. cxb4 Re8
{ ...Nd3+ is coming and Black is about to win the white queen and the game. } *

